<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REASSEMBLE - RIGHT REVERSE IDLER GEAR
        ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl13021rg" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="7">
        <title>RIGHT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If required, replace the idler bearing and race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021h1">Figure 171</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021h1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021h1" filename="../figg13/G13021H1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 171. Idler Bearing &#38; Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear thrust washer on the idler shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021h2">Figure 172</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021h2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021h2" filename="../figg13/G13021H2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 172. Rear Thrust Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing inner race on the idler shaft and insert shaft into the case bore,
                threaded end of shaft to the front. As the idler shaft is moved forward, install the reverse idler gear
                on the shaft, long hub to the front and seating on the bearing inner race. Position the thrust washer on
                the shaft between the gear and support boss in the case and continue with movement of the idler shaft
                forward into the bore of the support boss (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021h3">Figure 173</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021h3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021h3" filename="../figg13/G13021H3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 173. Bearing Inner Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Making sure that the reverse idler shaft is seated in the bore of support boss and forward
                as far as possible, install the washer and stop nut on the front of the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021h4">Figure 174</hotlnk>). Tighten nut to 50 to 60 ft-lbs. (68 to 81 N&#8226; m).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021h4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021h4" filename="../figg13/G13021H4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 174. Install Washer &#38; Stop Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the idler shaft plug in the end of the shaft and tighten (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021h5">Figure 175</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021h5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021h5" filename="../figg13/G13021H5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 175. Idler Shaft Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the outer race of the auxiliary countershaft front bearing into the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021h6">Figure 176</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021h6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021h6" filename="../figg13/G13021H6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 176. Auxiliary Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Mark the countershaft drive gear for timing purposes. On the drive gear of each countershaft
                        assembly, mark the tooth aligned with the keyway of the gear and stamped with an "O" for easy
                        identification (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f13021h7">Figure 177</hotlnk>). A highly visible color of toolmaker's dye is
                        recommended for making timing marks.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f13021h7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021h7" filename="../figg13/G13021H7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 177. Mark Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
